== Meeting Notes ==

PostGIS - June 16, 2026

https://etherpad.mit.edu/p/OwAepwrXGB
=== Core PostGIS

  * postgis_tiger_geocoder and address_standardizer are now separate repositories
  * https://github.com/postgis/address_standardizer
  * https://gitea.osgeo.org/postgis/postgis_tiger_geocoder
* Current state
  * One postgis repo and one RPM/DEB includes several exensions (postgis, address_standardizer, postgis_tiger_geocoder)
* Future state
  * Three repos (postgis, address_standardizer, postgis_tiger_geocoder) for three RPM/DEB files, for three extensions
  * Have the address_standardizer, postgis_tiger_geocoder RPM/DEB weakly depend on the postgis RPM for minimum impact to users
* Concern for users relying on SELECT postgis_extensions_upgrade(); now that it will no longer
  upgrade postgis_tiger_geocoder and address_standardizer
  * we could update the postgis_extensions_upgrade() function to NOT bail out but rather print a warning with instruction about installing the required extension (needs ticket)
* Now they are separate from postgis package how to inform users they have to install these separately
  * Don't, have the postgis RPM (weakly) depend on the address_standardizer and postgis_tiger_geocoder RPMs
  * For yum - Devrim says they'll continue to package address_standardizer and postgis_tiger_geocoder as part of postgis package but with weak dependency so on install, it will mention and user has choice to say no to those. Also means these could be installed separately by user.
  * Windows PostGIS Bundle will continue to have all as part of PostGIS 3.7.0, so no impact to windows users aside from the postgis_extensions_upgrade() no longer upgrading these.

* Address sfcgal 2.3.0 regression failures on Debian - Darafei has fix [https://trac.osgeo.org/postgis/ticket/6081 6081]
* LLM Policy - how do we answer to people why we don't need an LLM Policy
* AI Skills files should we keep in PostGIS repo or separate
 * Sandro is okay with them being in repo
 * Darafei says better in repo, cause our repo has higher ranking than any new repo would
 * Regina - likes in core repo because it should follow the same versioning, what is best practice may change from version to version as we add new functions or change behavior of old

=== GEOS

* GEOS should expose the git hash so postgis_full_version() can show it. Sandro to file ticket for GEOS to expose

    https://github.com/libgeos/geos/issues/1446

* GEOS 3.15.0beta1 after Dan pushes in curve support. Dan doesn't see it should cause an issue


=== Packaging

    1. Can we separately package postgis_sfcgal and postgis_raster from the other extensions?

        Yes, that would be nice, would clean up some dependency issues

    2. h3-pg packagers aware the URL changed: https://github.com/postgis/h3-pg

    3. Devrim will ask packagers list at large how they want to consume PostGIS / other extension release notifications

=== Release schedule

    Packagers requests:

     Please, do not release on Friday! Monday morning Europe best.

    * Warn upfront for security releases. (add to HOWTO_RELEASE!) - Devrim to provide email we can use to reach PostgreSQL packagers

    * Improve support matrix on the PostGIS wiki (add to HOWTO_RELEASE!)

    * Release PostGIS 3.7.0alpha1 in July

=== Goals ===

   * Beat PostgreSQL 19 to release!
   * Release GEOS 3.15.0 by mid-July
   * Release postgis_tiger_geocoder and address_standardizer before end of June
   * Release PostGIS 3.7.0alpha1 by first of July
   * Release PostGIS 3.7.0beta1 by first of August (or freeze release beta?)
   * Release PostGIS 3.7.0 by end of August

=== Major Tasks Outstanding ===

==== GEOS ====

* GEOS release 3.15.0beta1 before end of June
* GEOS release 3.15.0rc1 early to mid July
* GEOS release 3.15.0 mid to later July



==== PostGIS ====

* address_standardizer - release before end of June
* postgis_tiger_geocoder - 2015.1 - release before end of June
* PostGIS 3.17.0alpha1 - release later June / early July
* PostGIS 3.17.0beta1 - release late July
* PostGIS 3.17.0rc1 - Early August
* PostGIS 3.17.0 - Mid / Late August
* Improve support matrix on the PostGIS wiki
==== SFCGAL ====

* SFCGAL 2.3.0 already released, just confirm [https://gitea.osgeo.org/postgis/postgis/commit/c8ea8a68f1b56b142988a8d1e61656a73f5084f5 Darafei's fixes] fixes outstanding [https://trac.osgeo.org/postgis/ticket/6081 Debian issues] before we release PostGIS 3.17.0alpha1





